# .env file format

```bash
GEMINI_API_KEY="<gemini_api_key>"

LANGSMITH_TRACING=true
LANGSMITH_ENDPOINT="https://api.smith.langchain.com"
LANGSMITH_API_KEY="<langsmith_api_key>"
LANGSMITH_PROJECT="<langsmith_project_name>"

INDEX_NAME="<pinecone_index_name>"
PINECONE_API_KEY="<pinecone_api_key>"
```

Replace the placeholder values with your actual credentials and project details. Also make sure the `.env` file is included in your `.gitignore` file.

* `gemini_api_key` can be generated from Google AI Studio:
  https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey

* `langsmith_api_key` can be generated from LangSmith:
  https://smith.langchain.com

* `langsmith_project_name` is the project name you want traces to be associated with.

* `pinecone_index_name` is the name of the Pinecone index you created.

* `pinecone_api_key` can be generated from the Pinecone Console:
  https://app.pinecone.io

